  "prompt": "Is there anything I can buy that will make water boil faster?",
  "response": "There are a few things that can help water boil slightly faster:\n\n1. An electric kettle - These are generally faster than stovetop methods.\n\n2. A pot with a wider base and thinner bottom can help distribute heat more evenly.\n\n3. Using a lid traps heat and reduces boiling time.\n\n4. Starting with hot tap water instead of cold water can save some time.\n\n5. Some specialty \"rapid boil\" pots or induction cooktops claim to boil water faster.\n\nHowever, the differences are usually only minutes at most, and the most significant factor is the power of your heat source.",
